    "instruction": "For each of metric.csv, trace.csv, and log.csv compute compact per-series global statistics using the full available series (no time filtering):\n1) metric.csv: group by cmdb_id and kpi_name and compute count, global P95, global P5, mean, max. Return the top 20 component-KPI pairs sorted by count (include columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, count, p95, p5, mean, max). Also return total number of distinct kpi_name and distinct cmdb_id in metric.csv.\n2) trace.csv: group by cmdb_id and trace_name and compute count, P95, P5, mean, max. Return top 20 by count with same columns. Also return total distinct trace_name and cmdb_id.\n3) log.csv: group by cmdb_id and log_name and compute count, P95, P5, mean, max (value column). Return top 20 by count. Also return total distinct log_name and cmdb_id.\n4) error_logs.csv: return counts per cmdb_id (how many error log rows per cmdb_id), earliest timestamp per cmdb_id, and show up to 20 rows of the error_logs (columns: timestamp, cmdb_id, message) ordered by timestamp asc. Limit all returned rows to at most 20. Keep output as compact tables. Do not filter by the incident time window yet."
